<TEXT>
outrage grew wednesday over the robberykilling of 
a pregnant suburban lawyer and the wounding of her husband while 
their baby born by caesarean section struggled for survival 
in housing developments in posh hotels in student haunts and 
in the streets the talk was of the attack on carol stuart and her 
husband chuck who were abducted as they left a childbirth class 
at brigham and womens hospital monday night 
their assailant forced them to drive into the inner city area 
bordering the hospital there the assailant robbed the couple and 
shot stuart in the abdomen his 33yearold wife in the head 
stuart 29 remained in critical condition wednesday a boston 
city hospital spokesman said 
late in the day police superintendent joseph saia said 
detectives had been able to narrow the list of suspects down to a 
chosen few after speaking to stuart at his hospital bedside 
more than 400 people gathered wednesday evening for a memorial 
mass at a church in the same innercity neighborhood were the 
attack occurred 
the community wanted to pray for the families we thought a 
mass would be the best way to do that said the rev joseph 
krastel rector of the mission roman catholic church 
it hit home beryl cohen a prominent boston attorney said 
wednesday as he made his way through the downtown shopping 
district miles from the site of the crime its not a suburban 
story its not about rich and poor its not madefortelevision 
fiction i just called my son who takes guitar lessons on tremont 
street near the shooting and told him to be careful 
in the mission hill area where police found the couple shot and 
slumped in their car 23year old anthony stanley was standing 
outside a liquor store with a friend wednesday 
the man who did it should be taken out we got to get the 
death penalty back the guy was foul he had no heart said 
stanley 
at a downtown cutlery store proprietor arthur marks said his 
employees could talk about nothing but the crime and its brutality 
its almost too hard to look the 73yearold merchant said 
because of its enormity and the fact that its so needless 
chuck stuart 29yearold general manager of a fur store used a 
car phone to call police family members said the telephone was 
installed in mrs stuarts car after she became pregnant so she 
could remain in touch with her husband 
several hours after the shooting a son christopher was born 
the mother died shortly after the birth hospital spokeswomen would 
only say wednesday that the infant was alive family members said 
the baby had suffered seizures and there was diminishing hope for 
his survival 
neonatal experts said an infant delivered by caesarean section 
32 weeks after conception as christopher was should have a 98 
percent chance of surviving but mrs stuarts loss of blood in the 
shooting was said to harm the childs chances 
he looked perfect they told us to stroke his face because 
they said he would need a lot of love mrs stuarts aunt 
rosemary leone said after seeing the baby carol had been having 
a wonderful pregnancy she wanted this baby so badly but they 
dont think theres much hope for him 
