<TEXT>
a swarm of 40 earthquakes struck the 
yellowstone national park area but only two were strong enough to 
be felt geologists said 
the quakes began at 116 pm mdt tuesday and were recorded 
during the next nine hours said walter nagy who monitors 
yellowstone seismic activity for the university of utah seismograph 
stations 
the quakes included two of magnitude 35 on the richter scale of 
ground movement at 935 pm and 936 pm these were large enough 
to be felt locally he said 
the quakes were six miles north of west yellowstone mont 
along the western boundary of the park 
they struck within five miles of an extensive swarm sequence in 
1985 which included 28 quakes of magnitude 35 or greater nagy 
said 
he said tuesdays quakes were at the eastern end of the rupture 
zone of the magnitude 75 hebgen quake on aug 17 1959 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude 
an earthquake of 35 on the richter scale can cause slight 
damage in the local area a 7 reading is a major earthquake 
capable of widespread heavy damage 8 is a great quake capable 
of tremendous damage 
the oct 17 san francisco bay area quake measured 71 on the 
richter scale 
</TEXT>
