their continuing massive superiority in shortrange nuclear missile 
systems 
we therefore called again on the soviet union to reduce 
unilaterally its shortrange missile systems to current nato 
levels the statement said 
the ministers agenda was somewhat overshadowed by soviet 
foreign minister eduard shevardnadzes unusually candid speech on 
monday 
he told the soviet legislature that the krasnoyarsk radar 
station violated the 1972 ussoviet antiballistic missile treaty 
and said it would be removed the facility stood in the way of 
further arms treaties he said 
it was an acknowledgement of what the united states has 
maintained for a long time said a senior us official speaking 
on condition of anonymity 
we obviously applaud this recognition and the pledge to 
dismantle the installation he said 
west german defense minister gerhard stoltenberg called 
shevardnadzes speech remarkable and a true sign of glasnost 
openness 
the fact that he stands up and says straight out that 
krasnoyarsk was a violation of the abm treaty is a whole new 
language he told reporters 
shevardnadze said the decision to take down the giant 
phasedarray radar had been criticized internally but he said 
we are saving the abm treaty and opening the way to the 
conclusion of a treaty on strategic weapons 
the united states has argued the abm treaty prohibited the 
deployment of large radar stations capable of giving early 
warnings of missile attacks anywhere except on the periphery of 
us or soviet territory the krasnoyarsk radar is deep within 
soviet siberia 
in his speech shevardnadze also called for dissolving nato and 
the sovietled warsaw pact 
not surprisingly the nato officials did not share his vision of 
an end to the western allliance 
i can assure you were not thinking of disbanding nato 
stoltenberg said 
all 16 nato nations except france attended the meeting france 
does not belong to the alliances integrated military structure 
iceland which has no armed forces has observer status 
