<TEXT>
buddy was no ordinary tomcat at 6 years 
old hed survived two broken jaws innumerable fights a fall from 
a fourthstory window and various internal injuries 
but buddy like many family pets was powerless to fight the 
enemy he faced at 504 pm on oct 17 
the 71magnitude bay area earthquake that took dozens of lives 
injured thousands and caused more than 7 billion damage also 
claimed a large number of pets 
just like human victims pets were trapped in falling buildings 
consumed by fires and crushed in cars but perhaps the largest 
numbers were swallowed by panic in a world gone temporarily haywire 
buddy and another cat a spayed female named poochie lived in 
an apartment building partially demolished by fire the night of the 
quake it has since been razed said buddys veterinarian lee 
morris 
they esccaped from the burning apartment both cats ran 
outdoors buddy died he was burned they found his body its 
pretty ironic that he didnt make it through this because if 
anybody could have it would have been him morris said 
poochie did survive when her owner went back in for 15 
minutes before they wrecked the building she had come back she 
poochies owner brought her in on thursday she smelled like 
smoke but she was ok morris said 
what was nightmarish about the quake was not only did we 
scare the bejesus out of the cats and dogs but we lost power 
said rich avanzino president of the san francisco society for the 
prevention of cruelty to animals 
disoriented animals rushing hither and yon were crossing 
streets with abandon coming upon motorists who no longer had the 
benefit of street lights avanzino said 
several veterinarians told the story of spot a black 
3yearold female cat who like dockworker buck helm defied odds 
to survive 
spot was sunning herself on an apartment building windowsill 
avanzino said she was dislodged and fell 10 floors to the 
concrete she was rushed here and came out with only a broken leg 
thats one lucky cat he said 
dr john holden at mission pet hospital treated about 20 
fourlegged quake victims there were some traumatic injuries 
one cat was crushed under boxes there were a lot of glass 
injuries he said 
the cat crushed by boxes came in pretty gorked out but hes 
doing better neurologically he added 
he is sure many pets have yet to be found no one will ever know 
how many dogs cats guinea pigs fish birds reptiles and other 
pets were killed in the quake he said 
at least two dozen animals who bolted from their homes during 
the quake have been reunited with their owners by san francisco 
animal care and control said director carl friedman a dozen more 
are being cared for by the agency 
avanzino and other spca employees spent the night of the temblor 
in quake zones handing out pet food leashes cat carriers 
dishes bowls and water he said 
since then the spca has been working to arrange for temporary 
homes for animals whose owners were left homeless avanzino said 
dan harberts owner of bubbling well pet memorial park in napa 
said he had arranged for the burials of at least two dogs who died 
of earthquakerelated injuries 
the veterinarians said there were few ways to protect pets from 
earthquake injury or death its important to have carriers or ways 
to confine animals in an emergency holden said and returning to 
normal as quickly as possible will help an animal after a quake 
morris whose patients in addition to poochie included a dog who 
went through a window and cut up his nose and several cats who 
pulled their toenails out in struggles to get away said the best 
thing owners can do is offer to your pets the same comfort now 
that they have always offered you 
and he added dont be upset if a pet hides cowers refuses 
food pouts mopes vomits or wets where he or she shouldnt for a 
while 
ive talked to about 30 people who describe psychological 
problems with their pets in some cases the people are stressed 
and are reading their own problems into their pets morris said 
