<TEXT>
labor secretary elizabeth dole today named w 
j usery jr a longtime mediator and onetime labor secretary 
himself as supermediator for the 6monthold strike by the 
united mine workers against pittston coal group 
i believe that bill usery is precisely the right person to 
assist the parties in resolving what has thus far been a most 
difficult dispute mrs dole told reporters in making the 
announcement 
usery who agreed tuesday to try to settle the strike by 1700 
miners in three states said the public acrimony between the union 
and company gave him pause before he decided to accept 
this is one that you didnt jump at so quick usery said 
still usery said he would contact both sides immediately and that 
he hoped to resolve the strike before the upcoming holidays usery 
said he would meet separately with company and union officials 
first but wanted them to agree to a facetoface meeting soon 
usery labor secretary in the ford administration has an 
impressive record of settling strikes since leaving government he 
has headed a labor relations company in washington 
his skills will be tested in the umwpittston dispute the two 
sides refuse to negotiate facetoface and have been shuttling 
messages through federal mediators 
the strike began april 5 at pittston mines in virginia west 
virginia and kentucky the major dispute is over health and 
retirement benefits 
two weeks ago mrs dole met with strikers in carbo va and 
days later sat down with umw president richard trumka and pittston 
chairman paul douglas after that meeting she said she would name 
a supermediator 
as labor secretary usery sometimes stepped into contract 
disputes but mrs dole has resisted doing so 
i am not a mediator she said during her visit to the 
pittston facility im not here to say i have the answer to this 
complex problem but i do feel now it is time to see if we can 
facilitate the bargaining process 
userys resume includes helping end a sixmonth strike by the 
united auto workers against deere amp co in 1987 and a threeweek 
strike by chicago teachers in 1983 
he also helped settle a professional football strike in 1974 and 
has mediated dozens of disputes in the rubber auto electric 
hotel and transportation industries 
president nixon brought the hardwick ga native to washington 
in 1969 naming him assistant secretary of labor he was credited 
with helping settle railroad and airline labor disputes 
in 1973 he was named director of the federal mediation and 
conciliation service serving for three years until ford tapped him 
to head the labor department 
