<TEXT>
a nineblock residential area was strewn 
with smoldering debris today after a series of explosions destroyed 
three homes killing two people and injuring 13 others 
its like a war zone theres a lot of damage conneaut 
mayor lewis shiley said after surveying the neighborhood 
a dozen agents from the us bureau of alcohol tobacco and 
firearms were to search the rubble later today for clues of the 
explosion shiley said the mayor said it was presumed there were 
no more deaths officials earlier feared more victims might be in 
the wreckage 
its pretty much out theres still some smoldering chet 
arcaro conneaut building inspector said of the fire that broke 
out after the series of explosions about noon tuesday 
