<TEXT>
local governments that urged peasants to grow 
more grain are too short of cash to buy the bumper harvest leaving 
angry peasants with grain they cant sell or store an official 
report said wednesday 
ever since spring planting time chinese leaders have been 
urging peasants to grasp grain production and plant grain 
rather than more profitable crops in order to help china become 
selfsufficient in grain 
many peasants did and now they are mad the peasants daily 
said 
this years crop is estimated to top 400 million tons making it 
the highest since 1984 but because of the governments yearold 
economic austerity program which has sharply cut bank credit many 
county grain bureaus have no cash to buy the crop 
what they do buy they cant sell because regional grain bureaus 
the next step in the state purchase system also have no money 
the paper said 
county grain storage facilities are overflowing it said and in 
one county in central china 100000 tons are being stored in the 
open and face danger of turning moldy in another county peasants 
have been stuck with more than 100000 tons in their homes 
the states inability to buy the crop has depressed free market 
prices and in central chinas henan province some peasants have 
sold grain at firesale prices to itinerate profiteers to get it 
off their hands the paper said 
all peasants contract with the state to sell a fixed amount of 
grain but they can sell the rest on the free market in past 
years free market prices were higher than state prices and in some 
areas local governments had trouble keeping peasants from selling 
their entire crops on the free market 
the government fears that if all grain were bought and sold on 
free markets the price would rise and trigger unrest in cities 
where residents are used to low statesubsidized prices 
the paper noted the irony of the situation 
two months earlier large numbers of officials rode in 
propaganda buses through the villages mobilizing peasants to sell 
more grain to the state this year it wrote two months later 
when the peasants carried their extra grain to the grain shop the 
grain shops one after another were closed the peasants 
furiously asked isnt this making fun of us field hands 
county governments dealt with a similar shortage of funds last 
year by issuing ious but that triggered protests and violent 
clashes in some places this year the government pledged to pay 
cash so that not taking the grain at all has become its only 
option 
the government has compounded its headache by recreating a state 
monopoly on buying cotton this year to keep a shortage of cotton 
from driving prices up the move means local governments must come 
up with even more funds than before 
the official china daily said last week that the central bank 
was distributing 5 billion in emergency funds to local banks to 
help buy the harvest the peasants daily did not say if this sum 
would be enough 
it called the problem one of circulation and urged 
responsible departments to think of solutions as soon as 
possible 
