<TEXT>
president bushs veto of a bill to provide 
abortion assistance to impoverished victims of rape and incest was 
sustained in the house on wednesday as a 231191 vote to override 
him fell 51 votes short of the necessary twothirds margin 
though narrow in scope the bill carried symbolic importance in 
the widening political struggle over the abortion issue and 
proponents took their loss with a vow to keep the presidents feet 
to the fire but rep chris smith rnj called it a decisive 
victory for the prolife movement 
the president won a legislative victory today with use of a 
legislative minority said rep les aucoin dore he will put 
