when ames department stores inc decided to 
bring zayre stores into the corporate fold there were doubts that 
the discounter had selected an acquisition that would fit in easily 
or enhance its operations 
a year later ames is putting the finishing touches on what it 
calls the single largest us retail conversion ever on thursday 
254 former zayre stores will open their doors under the ames name 
the 12month process has turned ames into a dominant discounter 
in the northeast and the fourthbiggest discount retailer in the 
country with expected sales this year of 5 billion the three 
leading discounters are k mart corp walmart stores inc and the 
target stores division of dayton hudson corp 
peter b hollis ames president and chief executive officer 
said integrating zayres has demonstrated ames ability to handle 
change a necessary skill for mass merchants to have in a business 
where prosperity depends on being able to adapt to shifting 
consumer tastes and shopping habits 
retailers who fail to change will fall by the wayside 
hollis said in an interview 
ames had considerable experience with acquisitions before it 
bought zayre corps discount store division in october 1988 for 
778 million about 500 of ames 693 stores in 20 states and 
washington were the products of acquisitions ames has doubled its 
size twice in the past 4 years 
we are a company that are accustomed to acquisition and we 
are accustomed to change said hollis 
