pan american world airways plans to add more than 
60 flights a week from miami as part of a winter schedule increase 
on many routes once dominated by strikehampered eastern airlines 
the carrier announced wednesday 
beginning oct 29 pan am will start three daily nonstop 
flights from miami international airport to philadelphia two daily 
nonstops to boston and a daily flight to raleigh nc and 
charlotte nc 
in addition the new yorkbased carrier plans to add a third 
daily flight between miami and washington dc service from new 
yorks kennedy airport to fort lauderdale fla also will begin 
sunday 
in the caribbean pan am plans to begin daily flights to the 
cayman islands st maarten and antigua 
also pan am plans to resume a weekly flight between miami and 
frankfurt west germany that was suspended several years ago 
by middecember pan am is scheduled to increase the number of 
daily flights out of florida to about 140 
pan am presently operates 96 daily flights from florida 
including 46 from miami the carriers busiest hub 
miamibased eastern is entering the ninth month of a strike by 
machinists flight attendants and pilots 
