compaq computer corp announced a 51 percent 
increase in earnings for the third quarter due partly to higher 
sales and investment earnings 
the houstonbased companys net income totaled 87 million or 
202 per share on sales of 683 million compared with earnings 
of 58 million or 140 per share on sales of 502 million in 
last years third quarter 
in the us compaq market share is at an alltime high 
said rod canion compaqs president and chief executive officer 
international sales accounted for 43 percent of the quarters 
sales and were up 74 percent from a year ago he added 
for the first nine months of this year compaq reported earnings 
of 254 million or 594 per share a 56 percent increase over the 
1633 million or 406 per share last year sales totaled 21 
billion up from 14 billion 
compaq said the earnings for the quarter and nine months include 
a nonrecurring pretax gain of 137 million resulting from an 
increase in the carrying value of the companys investment in 
conner peripherals inc the gains resulted from conners issuance 
of additional common stock at prices higher than the carrying value 
of conner common stock owned by compaq 
during the quarter compaq purchased the former wang 
laboratories manufacturing plant in stirling scotland which will 
be used for international service and repair operations 
compaq makes desktop portable and laptop personal computers 
that are sold in 56 countries through a worldwide network of more 
than 3000 authorized dealers 
