<TEXT>
investigators searching for the cause of 
a huge plastics plant explosion discovered three more bodies in the 
twisted rubble wednesday and continued the search for 17 others 
presumed killed 
in all five bodies have been found since a series of explosions 
ripped through the phillips petroleum co plant on monday 
company officials learned that one man who had been listed as 
missing was not at the plant at the time plant manager robert benz 
said 
assistant secretary of labor john scannell who heads the 
occupational safety and health administration toured the plant 
wednesday with other federal investigators sent in by us labor 
secretary elizabeth dole 
its total devastation scannell said in 30 years of 
experience in the chemical industry ive never seen such massive 
equipment twisted and strung about 
its still a very hazardous situation with twisted steel and 
columns the total destruction of some parts you can only imagine 
the force of the explosion bolts were sheared right off and 
twisted like pretzels 
the plant which produced 45 million pounds of plastics a day 
exploded in a series of blasts monday afternoon throwing metal and 
concrete debris as far as six miles miles of twisted strings of 
pipe are piled haphazardly around the plant some buildings are 
gone and eight giant chemical reactors vessels look like huge 
battered tin cans 
osha had a team of 15 investigators including chemical and 
structural engineers at the site scannell said they will help 
with recovery operations and offer technical assistance and advice 
and then we want to determine a cause scannell said we 
want to come up with prevention efforts to keep this from occurring 
again 
virtually every piece of material is being looked at as a 
piece of the puzzle scannell said adding the osha crew expects 
to remain at the site for several days well be here as long as 
it takes 
the area where authorities believe most of the 18 missing 
workers are is a twisted jumble of rubble and debris scannell said 
the recovery of victims could be days could be weeks its very 
complicated part of the problem is that when one piece of 
wreckage is moved it sets off a chain reaction of falling debris 
scannell said 
on wednesday the body of one of three contract workers 
unaccounted for since the explosions was found in a maintenance 
area in the morning the two other bodies were found separately 
later in the day but both were in the same vicinity near a storage 
area for polyethylene pellets said bill wicker another company 
spokesman 
two other bodies were located earlier in the week the 
identities of the dead have not been released 
officials dont know yet exactly what caused the explosions 
flammable ethylene and isobutane gases escaped from a leaking 
chemical reactor but phillips officials said they dont know how 
the gases were ignited 
the plant manager repeated previous comments that the plant had 
an excellent safety record that included a 5 millionmanhour 
stretch with no safetyrelated work injuries that cost an employee 
work time that would cover a period of some 2 years benz said 
but union officials say they are questioning work schedules that 
may have left less experienced or tired employees on the job 
our members tell us of long hours cutbacks on staff and the 
utilization of subcontractors within the plant said bob wages 
national vice president of the oil chemical and atomic workers 
union wed like to know if these were contributing factors to 
the accident 
phillips spokesman jere smith said the company likely will 
rebuild at the site but he was uncertain what type of facility 
would replace the plastics plant 
the plants 900 workers will continue to be paid for at least 
two months he said but some may be laid off later phillips will 
try to find work for some of them at the companys other operations 
in houston and sweeny 
</TEXT>
